A few short clips from our trip to #melbourne doesn’t feel like we have been here for as long as we have. The public transport is amazing by the way, highly recommend it if you come. AFL is pretty cool too if you like sports, kind of hard to follow so I’d do a little research before. The botanical garden downtown and all of the graffiti art is astounding. Overall a fantastic and well built city, from art to infrastructure. One more thing, the amount of hidden bars is staggering so you’ll never run low on cool places to grab a drink.

#1 Have all of your stationary and wedding attire in one location so we can grab it quickly to photograph it as efficiently as possible 
#2 Keep your area clean because we all know that clean photos are better photos (usually) 
#3 Have someone (usually maid of honor) help with your dress throughout the bridal photo process, this helps so much alleviate stress and you get some great photos of you and your best friend. 
#4 Drink plenty of water, we know receptions can lead to headaches on the next day often times. 
#5 Most importantly, do not stress! As long as you get down the aisle and you get married that’s the most significant part of the day. Everything else WILL fall into place! So relax and let all of your hard working vendors take care of everything.

I’ve shot so many weddings and very seldom do I make a good friend through all the consultations and planning process. Meet our client Hunter Hart @hunterhartphoto, a brilliant self-taught photographer based in Nashville, Tennessee. You may already know Hunter from the insightful interview we’ve shared earlier this year, where he talks about his artistic journey and how his mental health impacts his creative work.

With his photojournalistic approach, Hunter presents human emotions in a beautiful, raw way. He’s been with Pixieset for over 5 years and enjoys the possibility to have everything under one roof. From photo delivery to selling prints, managing contracts and invoices, and building a website.

In @hunterhartphoto’s words, “having all these things together is just a game changer and it makes your life so much easier.” If you’re ready to simplify your photography workflow, go to pixieset.com and start exploring all our powerful tools. ⚡️
